an50GenUBR.name: an50GenUBR
an50GenUBR.description: Indicates the system's current uncoded burst rate. With adaptive modulation enabled, this rate may change over time, depending on the prevailing propagation conditions.

an50GenRFLink.name: an50GenRFLink
an50GenRFLink.description: connected(2) indicates the terminal is communicating properly to the remote terminal. notConnected(1) indicates there is no communication with the remote terminal.

an50GenFrequency.name: an50GenFrequency
an50GenFrequency.description: The frequency which represents the operating channel of the link. The system can be configured to operate over 9 distinct channels.

an50GenAllignmentMode.name: an50GenAllignmentMode
an50GenAllignmentMode.description: Specifies if the antenna alignment is done with buzzer or voltage.

an50GenEncryptionEnabled.name: an50GenEncryptionEnabled
an50GenEncryptionEnabled.description: Specifies if encryption is enabled or not.

an50GenFlowControlEnabled.name: an50GenFlowControlEnabled
an50GenFlowControlEnabled.description: This attribute specifies if flow control is enabled or not.

an50GenHttpAccessEnabled.name: an50GenHttpAccessEnabled
an50GenHttpAccessEnabled.description: This attribute specifies if Http Access is enabled or not.

an50GenTelnetAccessEnabled.name: an50GenTelnetAccessEnabled
an50GenTelnetAccessEnabled.description: This attribute specifies if Telnet Access is enabled or not.

an50GenTelnetPort.name: an50GenTelnetPort
an50GenTelnetPort.description: This attribute specifies the Telnet port number.

an50GenOptionsKey.name: an50GenOptionsKey
an50GenOptionsKey.description: This attribute specifies the Product Options Key.

an50GenResetDevice.name: an50GenResetDevice
an50GenResetDevice.description: reset(2) indicates to reset the AN50 terminal. donothing(1) indicates do not reset AN50 terminal.

an50GenFault.name: an50GenFault
an50GenFault.description: The attribute specifies the Fault LED status of the terminal.

an50GenTxPower.name: an50GenTxPower
an50GenTxPower.description: This object specifies the actual Tx Power of the AN-50 Node in ?

an50GenRegisteredStations.name: an50GenRegisteredStations
an50GenRegisteredStations.description: This object specifies the actual number of configured links.

an50GenRegisteredConnections.name: an50GenRegisteredConnections
an50GenRegisteredConnections.description: This object specifies the actual number of configured connections.

an50GenActiveWirelessLinks.name: an50GenActiveWirelessLinks
an50GenActiveWirelessLinks.description: This object specifies the actual number of provisioned links.

an50GenChannelAutoScan.name: an50GenChannelAutoScan
an50GenChannelAutoScan.description: This object specifies the Auto-Scanning feature for the channel.

an50GenIduType.name: an50GenIduType
an50GenIduType.description: This object specifies the Indoor Unit Type.

an50GenOduType.name: an50GenOduType
an50GenOduType.description: This object specifies the Outdoor Unit Type.

an50EtherMacAddress.name: an50EtherMacAddress
an50EtherMacAddress.description: This object specifies the Ethernet MAC address of the local terminal.

an50EtherGateway.name: an50EtherGateway
an50EtherGateway.description: The IP Gateway of the AN-50 This field is used to specify the IP address of the gateway which the AN-50 is communicating through the core network.

an50EtherPortStatus.name: an50EtherPortStatus
an50EtherPortStatus.description: The attribute specifies the status of the Ethernet Port of the AN50.

an50EtherIP.name: an50EtherIP
an50EtherIP.description: The IP address of the AN-50. The default address from the factory is 192.168.25.2. For the initial set-up, the terminal should not be connected to the Internet network, i.e. the host computer should be connected directly to the terminal Ethernet port, to avoid address conflicts with other devices in a public network. Once the IP address has been set, the terminal can be connected to the core network, where it can receive either static or dynamic addressing (DHCP) in future configuration updates.

an50EtherMask.name: an50EtherMask
an50EtherMask.description: The IP Subnet Mask of the AN-50. The value is typically set to 255.255.255.0 (Class C subnet), which prevents certain local devices from going out into the wireless network.

an50Ether100.name: an50Ether100
an50Ether100.description: This object specifies the 100 Mb/s Ethernet LED status of the AN50.

an50EtherFd.name: an50EtherFd
an50EtherFd.description: The object specifies the Ethernet FullDuplex LED status of the AN50.

an50EtherMgmVidEn.name: an50EtherMgmVidEn
an50EtherMgmVidEn.description: The attribute specifies the Ethernet Management Vlan Enabled Status of the AN50.

an50EtherMgmVid.name: an50EtherMgmVid
an50EtherMgmVid.description: The attribute specifies the Ethernet Management Vlan Id of the AN50.

an50EtherLben.name: an50EtherLben
an50EtherLben.description: The attribute specifies the Link Backup Enable Status of the AN50.

an50WrlsChannel.name: an50WrlsChannel
an50WrlsChannel.description: specifies the operating channel of the system, within the 100 MHz available in the 5.8GHz UNII band. To avoid interference, two PTP links operating in the same physical location (co-located) or within close proximity (e.g. across the street) must be separated by at least one channel, i.e. the gap between channels should be 20 MHz or more (e.g. channels 1 and 3).

an50WrlsTxPower.name: an50WrlsTxPower
an50WrlsTxPower.description: The Tx Power of the AN-50 in dBm. Specifies the power level of the system, which is preset at the factory and should not be altered. In the event that this parameter needs to be changed, please contact the Redline support team.

an50WrlsModReduction.name: an50WrlsModReduction
an50WrlsModReduction.description: The Modulation Reduction Level of the AN-50. Applies when the Adaptive rate is disabled. Specifies how many levels the system must drop in modulation before beginning re-transmission to address packet errors. The value can be set from 1-7, with 2 being the typical value.

an50WrlsAdaptiveMod.name: an50WrlsAdaptiveMod
an50WrlsAdaptiveMod.description: Setting this attribute to AdaptiveRate(2) sets the system to operate in adaptive modulation mode. It is recommended to keep the AN-50 in this mode so that the system can automatically adjust the modulation level to the highest possible data rate based on measured RF performance. The user can define the minimum desired modulation level by setting the Main rate parameter. If the system meets this data rate, then the Signal LED on the front panel will light continuously green. If packet errors exceed one out of a million, the system will automatically lower the modulation level to maintain the link. In this case, the LED will flash green. If errors continue when the system reaches the lowest modulation level, the LED will flash red to indicate a failed RF link. The user can also disable the dynamic modulation mode by disabling Adaptive Modulation. In this mode, the user is required to set the Burst Rate and the Modulation Reduction Level. It is recommended not to operate the system in manual mode, as this mode is intended primarily for field support. Note the Signal LED will light solid green when the packet error rate is less than 1 out of a million. When the errors exceed this limit, the LED will not illuminate, indicating the RF link has failed.

an50WrlsUBR.name: an50WrlsUBR
an50WrlsUBR.description: This object contains the desired net uncoded burst rate for the link. Set uncoded burst rate in steps (0=6Mb/s, 1=9Mb/s, 2=12Mb/s, 3=18Mb/s, 4=24Mb/s, 5=36Mb/s, 6=48Mb/s, 7=54Mbs).

an50WrlsMaster.name: an50WrlsMaster
an50WrlsMaster.description: The object contains the configured mode of the AN50 terminal. 1 = PTP Slave, 2 = PTP Master, 3 = PMP Slave, 4 = PMP Master

an50WrlsVersion.name: an50WrlsVersion
an50WrlsVersion.description: Sets the version of the AN50 system software. The software can be remotely downloaded into the AN50. The system comprises sufficient memory to hold two independent software loads. The operator can specify which load to set as the active version.

an50WrlsEncryptCode.name: an50WrlsEncryptCode
an50WrlsEncryptCode.description: The object contains the Encryption Key used for the AN-50 terminal. Enter the MAC address of the remote terminal to enable over-the-air data encryption.

an50WrlsCableAttenuation.name: an50WrlsCableAttenuation
an50WrlsCableAttenuation.description: This object contains the Cable Attenuation for the AN-50 in dB.

an50WrlsRfPortStatus.name: an50WrlsRfPortStatus
an50WrlsRfPortStatus.description: The object specifies the status of the AN50s Wireless Port.

an50WrlsSaveConfig.name: an50WrlsSaveConfig
an50WrlsSaveConfig.description: The object saves the entire config set of the AN50.

an50WrlsActivateConfig.name: an50WrlsActivateConfig
an50WrlsActivateConfig.description: The object activates the entire config set of the AN50.

an50WrlsRadioEnable.name: an50WrlsRadioEnable
an50WrlsRadioEnable.description: The object specifies whether radio transmission is enabled or disabled.

an50WrlsRfStatusErrorCode.name: an50WrlsRfStatusErrorCode
an50WrlsRfStatusErrorCode.description: The object specifies the Error Code for the RF Status.

an50WrlsRfSignal.name: an50WrlsRfSignal
an50WrlsRfSignal.description: The object specifies the Wireless Signal LED status.

an50WrlsLMU.name: an50WrlsLMU
an50WrlsLMU.description: This object specifies the Link measurements unit (mile / Km).

an50WrlsLL.name: an50WrlsLL
an50WrlsLL.description: This object specifies the Link Length. See an50WrlsLMU object for units.

an50WrlsFrameSize.name: an50WrlsFrameSize
an50WrlsFrameSize.description: This object specifies the size of wireless frame (DL+RTD+UL) in micro seconds.

an50WrlsMinBlockSize.name: an50WrlsMinBlockSize
an50WrlsMinBlockSize.description: This object specifies a minimum number of bytes comprising transmitted block.

an50WrlsDownlinkSize.name: an50WrlsDownlinkSize
an50WrlsDownlinkSize.description: This object specifies the size of downlink sub-frame in micro seconds.

an50WrlsRoundTripDelay.name: an50WrlsRoundTripDelay
an50WrlsRoundTripDelay.description: This object specifies the round trip delay in micro seconds.

an50WrlsAdaptiveDLSize.name: an50WrlsAdaptiveDLSize
an50WrlsAdaptiveDLSize.description: This object specifies if adaptive downlink size is enabled or disabled.

an50WrlsExtSyncronize.name: an50WrlsExtSyncronize
an50WrlsExtSyncronize.description: This object specifies if external synchronization is enabled or disabled.

an50WrlsMaximumDistance.name: an50WrlsMaximumDistance
an50WrlsMaximumDistance.description: This object specifies the maximum distance between base station and subscriber station in Km.

an50WrlsRegistrationPeriod.name: an50WrlsRegistrationPeriod
an50WrlsRegistrationPeriod.description: This object specifies the number of frames between registration periods.

an50WrlsBroadcastDLCIR.name: an50WrlsBroadcastDLCIR
an50WrlsBroadcastDLCIR.description: This object specifies the broadcast downlink commited rate in kb/s.

an50WrlsBroadcastDLPIR.name: an50WrlsBroadcastDLPIR
an50WrlsBroadcastDLPIR.description: This object specifies the broadcast downlink peak rate in kb/s.

an50WrlsDFSAction.name: an50WrlsDFSAction
an50WrlsDFSAction.description: This object specifies the action taken when another system is detected on the same frequency

an50WrlsATPEnabled.name: an50WrlsATPEnabled
an50WrlsATPEnabled.description: This object specifies if the Automatic Transmitted Power Control is enabled

an50ResetStatistics.name: an50ResetStatistics
an50ResetStatistics.description: A value of reset(2) resets the performance statistics on the AN-50, a value of donothing(1) does nothing.

an50PmEtherRxPackets.name: an50PmEtherRxPackets
an50PmEtherRxPackets.description: This object counts the number of ethernet packets successfully received by the local system.

an50PmEtherRxPacketsErr.name: an50PmEtherRxPacketsErr
an50PmEtherRxPacketsErr.description: This object counts the number of ethernet packet errors received by the local system.

an50PmEtherTxPackets.name: an50PmEtherTxPackets
an50PmEtherTxPackets.description: This object counts the number of Ethernet packets transmitted by the local system.

an50PmEtherTxPacketsErr.name: an50PmEtherTxPacketsErr
an50PmEtherTxPacketsErr.description: This object counts the number of Ethernet error packets transmitted by the local system.

an50PmEtherRxPacketsDisc.name: an50PmEtherRxPacketsDisc
an50PmEtherRxPacketsDisc.description: This object counts the number of ethernet packets discarded by receiver.

an50PmEtherTxPacketsDisc.name: an50PmEtherTxPacketsDisc
an50PmEtherTxPacketsDisc.description: This object counts the number of ethernet packets discarded by transmitter.

an50PmWrlsRxSigMin.name: an50PmWrlsRxSigMin
an50PmWrlsRxSigMin.description: This object indicates the minimum received signal strength measured since the last SNMP update.

an50PmWrlsRxSigMean.name: an50PmWrlsRxSigMean
an50PmWrlsRxSigMean.description: This object indicates the average received signal strength measured since the last SNMP update.

an50PmWrlsRxSigMax.name: an50PmWrlsRxSigMax
an50PmWrlsRxSigMax.description: This object indicates the maximum received signal strength measured since the last SNMP update

an50PmWrlsAvgSinAdr.name: an50PmWrlsAvgSinAdr
an50PmWrlsAvgSinAdr.description: This object indicates the average signal to noise ratio measured since the last SNMP update. The ratio is based on the digital information provided from the output of the AtoD converter.

an50PmWrlsRxPackets.name: an50PmWrlsRxPackets
an50PmWrlsRxPackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets received over the air from the remote terminal.

an50PmWrlsRxPacketsRetx.name: an50PmWrlsRxPacketsRetx
an50PmWrlsRxPacketsRetx.description: This object indicates the number of packets retransmitted over the air from the remoter terminal.

an50PmWrlsRxPacketsDisc.name: an50PmWrlsRxPacketsDisc
an50PmWrlsRxPacketsDisc.description: This object indicates the number of packets, originating from the remote terminal lost over the air due to degradation in the RF link.

an50PmWrlsTxPackets.name: an50PmWrlsTxPackets
an50PmWrlsTxPackets.description: This object indicates the number of wireless packets (including Ethernet frames and error correction bytes) transmitted over the air by the local terminal.

an50PmWrlsTxPacketsRetx.name: an50PmWrlsTxPacketsRetx
an50PmWrlsTxPacketsRetx.description: This object indicates the number of packets retransmitted over the air by the local terminal. The retransmission scheme is based on the Acknowledge/Request (ARQ) algorithm that detects when packets are lost and makes a request to the MAC scheduler to repeat transmission of the lost packets.

an50PmWrlsTxPacketsDisc.name: an50PmWrlsTxPacketsDisc
an50PmWrlsTxPacketsDisc.description: This object indicates the total number of packets lost over the air due to degradation in the RF link.

an50PmWrlsCalcDst.name: an50PmWrlsCalcDst
an50PmWrlsCalcDst.description: This object contains the calculated link distance.

an50SwServer.name: an50SwServer
an50SwServer.description: The address of the TFTP server used for software upgrades. If the address of the TFTP server is unknown, return 0.0.0.0.

an50SwFilename.name: an50SwFilename
an50SwFilename.description: The file name of the software image to be loaded into this device.

an50SwAdminStatus.name: an50SwAdminStatus
an50SwAdminStatus.description: If set to upgrade(2), the device will initiate a TFTP software image download using an50SwFilename. If the download process is interrupted by a reset or power failure, the device will load the previous image. If set to noUpgrade(1), the device will revert to the previous version of the software. At initial startup, this object has the default value of noUpgrade(1).

an50SwOperStatus.name: an50SwOperStatus
an50SwOperStatus.description: This object shows the download status. inProgress(1) indicates that a TFTP download is underway completeSuccess(2) indicates that the last software upgrade was successful failed(3) indicates that the last attempted download failed, ordinarily due to TFTP timeout.

an50SwCurrentVers.name: an50SwCurrentVers
an50SwCurrentVers.description: The software version currently operating in this device's flash. This object should be in the syntax used by the individual vendor to identify software versions. If it is not applicable, this MUST contain an empty string.

an50SwOtherVers.name: an50SwOtherVers
an50SwOtherVers.description: The software version in the secondary flash. This object should be in the syntax used by the individual vendor to identify software versions. If it is not applicable, this MUST contain an empty string.

an50SysLastTrapTime.name: an50SysLastTrapTime
an50SysLastTrapTime.description: The value of system.sysUpTime when the last trap was generated. If no traps have been generated since the last reset, this attribute has a value of 0. No trap is issued as a result of a change to this value.

an50TftpFailTrap.name: an50TftpFailTrap
an50TftpFailTrap.description: An event to report the failure of a Software Download.

an50TftpSuccessTrap.name: an50TftpSuccessTrap
an50TftpSuccessTrap.description: An event to report the success of a Software Download.

an50PswdChangeFailTrap.name: an50PswdChangeFailTrap
an50PswdChangeFailTrap.description: An event to report the failure of a password change.

an50FirmwareConfigFailTrap.name: an50FirmwareConfigFailTrap
an50FirmwareConfigFailTrap.description: An event to report the failure of a firmware config.

an50EepromCorruptedTrap.name: an50EepromCorruptedTrap
an50EepromCorruptedTrap.description: An event to report the corruption of the EEPROM.

an50PowerSupplyFailureTrap.name: an50PowerSupplyFailureTrap
an50PowerSupplyFailureTrap.description: An event to report the power supply failure.

an50SaveConfigTrap.name: an50SaveConfigTrap
an50SaveConfigTrap.description: An event to report the saving of configuration

an50ModifiedIDTrap.name: an50ModifiedIDTrap
an50ModifiedIDTrap.description: An event to report the modification in the configuration of a CID

an50pmpRegistrationMissed.name: an50pmpRegistrationMissed
an50pmpRegistrationMissed.description: An event to report the missing of the registration by a AN50 Subscriber to one BS.This trap is sent by the BS and contains the MAC address of the SS missing the registration

an50pmpRegistrationSuccessful.name: an50pmpRegistrationSuccessful
an50pmpRegistrationSuccessful.description: An event to report the successful registration of an AN50 Subscriber to BS. This trap is sent by the BS and contains the MAC address of the newly registered SS

an50DFSEvent.name: an50DFSEvent
an50DFSEvent.description: An event to report a dynamic frequency selection (DFS) event in AN50

an50MaxCid.name: an50MaxCid
an50MaxCid.description: The object contains the maximum number of CID for this equipment

an50LinkCurrentAvailId.name: an50LinkCurrentAvailId
an50LinkCurrentAvailId.description: The current available ID in the Links table that is queried by NMS before creating a new row in Link Table
